Package: snakeplot
Title: Serpentine (Snake) Plots for Survey and Activity Data
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mohammed", "Saqr", email = "saqr@saqr.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Sonsoles", "Lopez-Pernas",
           role = "aut"))
Description: Visualize survey responses and experience sampling data using
    serpentine (snake) layouts where horizontal bands alternate direction
    row-by-row, connected by U-turn arcs. Supports distribution bars,
    tick-mark plots, inter-item correlation arcs, faceted multi-construct
    panels, and daily time-of-day positioning for ecological momentary
    assessment data. Includes three bundled datasets from Neubauer and
    Schmiedek (2024) <doi:10.1007/s11618-023-01182-8>. Uses only base
    'R' graphics with zero external dependencies.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: graphics, grDevices, stats
LazyData: true
